==English==
===Etymology===
Coined erroneously in the early 20th century in confusion with the Hattites (Hattic) whose language was recorded in discovered texts as ''hasili''. The Hittites themselves called themselves ''nesili'' "pertaining to the city of Nesa",
hence the less popular alternative name [[Nesite]].

===Noun===
'''Hittite'''

#The Hittite people or language.

===Adjective===
'''Hittite'''

#Of or relating to the Hittite people, their language, or their kingdom in central Anatolia, modernday Turkey, that flourished from about 1800 to 1400 BCE.